<p>I have a Model that is called teams.</p>  <p>When I do Teams.account_ids it returns something like:</p>  <pre><code> [{"_id"=&gt;"145952912234658", "_type"=&gt;"Page"},  {"_id"=&gt;"465641870160985", "_type"=&gt;"Account"}] </code></pre>  <p>Lets say I want to get all Teams that have one specific account id regardless of its _type.</p>  <p>Something like:</p>  <pre><code>Team.where(some_id.in =&gt; account_ids.map{|k| k["_id")) </code></pre>